Here's a simple web app that features flying toasters using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript all embedded in a single file. This code creates an animation where toasters fly across the screen. You can simply copy and paste this code into an HTML file and open it in a web browser to see the effect.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Flying Toasters</title>
    <style>
        body {
            margin: 0;
            overflow: hidden;
            background-color: #87CEFA; /* Sky blue */
        }
        .toaster {
            position: absolute;
            width: 80px; /* Width of the toaster */
            height: 60px; /* Height of the toaster */
            background-image: url('https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f0/Toaster.svg/1200px-Toaster.svg.png'); /* URL to toaster image */
            background-size: cover;
            animation: fly 5s linear infinite;
        }

        @keyframes fly {
            from {
                transform: translateX(-100px) translateY(0);
                opacity: 1;
            }
            to {
                transform: translateX(100vw) translateY(-300px);
                opacity: 0;
            }
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <script>
        const createToaster = () => {
            const toaster = document.createElement('div');
            toaster.classList.add('toaster');

            // Randomize starting position
            const startY = Math.random() * window.innerHeight;
            toaster.style.top = `${startY}px`;

            // Append toaster to body
            document.body.appendChild(toaster);

            // Remove toaster after animation ends
            toaster.addEventListener('animationend', () => {
                toaster.remove();
            });
        };

        // Create toasters at a regular interval
        setInterval(createToaster, 1000);
    </script>
</body>
</html>
```

### Instructions:
1. Copy the entire code above.
2. Paste it into a new file and save it with a `.html` extension (e.g., `flying_toasters.html`).
3. Open the HTML file in a web browser.

Enjoy the flying toasters! You can adjust the animation timing or toaster image URL as needed.
